WEBVTT

1
00:00:04.140 --> 00:00:05.640
- I'm doing work in a brand-new way

2
00:00:05.640 --> 00:00:07.590
that I would not have done before.

3
00:00:07.590 --> 00:00:08.460
And so in this case,

4
00:00:08.460 --> 00:00:11.550
I would've not looked as
closely, frankly, at survey data,

5
00:00:11.550 --> 00:00:14.640
or stuck to my like, very stock reporting,

6
00:00:14.640 --> 00:00:16.530
so very often, you like look at,

7
00:00:16.530 --> 00:00:21.240
you have a survey that's
both like multiple-choice

8
00:00:21.240 --> 00:00:22.410
and open-response,

9
00:00:22.410 --> 00:00:26.550
and you kind of like say, "Well,
if this is a positive one,

10
00:00:26.550 --> 00:00:27.720
I might not look at the open-response,

11
00:00:27.720 --> 00:00:29.220
if it's a negative one, I'll dive in."

12
00:00:29.220 --> 00:00:31.860
Now I can treat kind of
all texts pretty equally,

13
00:00:31.860 --> 00:00:34.380
and look at things in a brand new way,

14
00:00:34.380 --> 00:00:36.360
and consider open-text responses,

15
00:00:36.360 --> 00:00:39.453
as a much, much richer
data source as it often is.